{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"non-stick frying pan, serving bowls, stove top","id":"r375225","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-8Jsv-WPKeDo\/XZMydIL5WeI\/AAAAAAAAalI\/Vi7EhAFumtMKciK8Hjnyb00qh30XQiOPwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DotmNu2Jl2zul7yq.png","title":"Turmeric cauliflower soup","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus 1-2 tablespoons extra for frying"},{"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"1 leek (approx. 160 g), white part only, cut into slices"},{"content":"2 potatoes (approx. 200 g), peeled and cut into pieces (3-5 cm)"},{"content":"1 tsp ground turmeric (see Tips)"},{"content":"½ tsp ground coriander"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground cumin"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground chilli (optional)"},{"content":"500 g cauliflower, broken into small florets"},{"content":"800 g liquid chicken stock (see Tips)"},{"content":"¼ tsp salt, to taste (see Tips)"},{"content":"2 pinches ground black pepper, to taste"},{"content":"1 brown onion, cut into thin slices, for garnishing"},{"content":"40 g cashews, for garnishing"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"11.9 g","fat":"17.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"14 g","calories":"1138.4 kJ \/ 271 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Place oil, leek and potato into mixing bowl and sauté <b>10 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b> or until leek just becomes translucent."},{"content":"Add turmeric, coriander, cumin and ground chilli (optional) and cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add cauliflower and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add liquid stock, salt and pepper and cook <b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, place a frying pan over medium-high heat. Add 1-2 tablespoons of oil, then add onions and cashews and fry until golden (approx. 5-8 minutes). Remove from pan and set aside."},{"content":"Allow soup to cool slightly, then blend <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>-<b>9, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 9<b> or until smooth. Divide between serving bowls and garnish with fried onions and cashews to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you have fresh turmeric on hand, you can use it instead of the ground turmeric. Simply use a 3 cm piece of peeled fresh turmeric and add it with the cauliflower in step 3.","You can replace liquid Chicken stock with chicken stock paste and water in this recipe. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Chicken stock paste recipe. In step 4 replace liquid stock with 1 tablespoon Chicken stock paste and 800 g water.","This soup is also perfect for the whole family. Just be sure to omit the salt and chop up the cashews and onion garnish if serving to younger children."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","4 portions"]}